{"title":"3.1 Convex Optimization","markdown":{"yaml":{"title":"3.1 Convex Optimization","format":{"pdf":{"documentclass":"article","number-sections":true,"pdf-engine":"lualatex","geometry":["top=30mm","left=25mm","right=25mm","bottom=30mm"]}}},"headingText":"Convex Optimization","containsRefs":false,"markdown":"\n\n{{< include ../_common.qmd >}}\n\n\n### Introduction\n\nConvex optimization is the study of minimizing convex functions over convex sets. The theory is elegant and the algorithms are efficient, making convex optimization a cornerstone of modern applied mathematics.\n\n### Convex Sets and Functions\n\n::: {#def-convex-set}\n## Convex Set\nA set $C \\subseteq \\R^n$ is **convex** if for all $\\bx, \\by \\in C$ and $\\theta \\in [0, 1]$:\n$$\n\\theta \\bx + (1 - \\theta) \\by \\in C\n$$\n:::\n\n::: {#def-convex-function}\n## Convex Function\nA function $f: \\R^n \\to \\R$ is **convex** if for all $\\bx, \\by \\in \\R^n$ and $\\theta \\in [0, 1]$:\n$$\nf(\\theta \\bx + (1 - \\theta) \\by) \\leq \\theta f(\\bx) + (1 - \\theta) f(\\by)\n$$\n:::\n\n### Optimality Conditions\n\n::: {#thm-first-order}\n## First-Order Optimality\nLet $f: \\R^n \\to \\R$ be convex and differentiable. Then $\\bx^*$ is a global minimizer if and only if:\n$$\n\\nabla f(\\bx^*) = \\mathbf{0}\n$$\n:::\n\n::: {#thm-second-order}\n## Second-Order Condition\nA twice-differentiable function $f$ is convex if and only if its Hessian is positive semidefinite everywhere:\n$$\n\\nabla^2 f(\\bx) \\succeq 0 \\quad \\text{for all } \\bx\n$$\n:::\n\n### Quadratic Programming\n\n::: {#def-qp}\n## Quadratic Program\nA **quadratic program** (QP) is an optimization problem of the form:\n$$\n\\begin{aligned}\n\\min_{\\bx} \\quad & \\frac{1}{2} \\bx^\\top \\mathbf{P} \\bx + \\mathbf{q}^\\top \\bx \\\\\n\\text{s.t.} \\quad & \\bA \\bx = \\mathbf{b} \\\\\n& \\mathbf{G} \\bx \\leq \\mathbf{h}\n\\end{aligned}\n$$\nThe problem is convex if $\\mathbf{P} \\succeq 0$.\n:::\n\n### Exercises\n\n::: {#exr-least-squares}\n## Least Squares as QP\nShow that the least squares problem $\\min_\\bx \\norm{\\bA\\bx - \\mathbf{b}}^2$ is a convex QP and derive the normal equations.\n:::\n","srcMarkdownNoYaml":"\n\n{{< include ../_common.qmd >}}\n\n## Convex Optimization\n\n### Introduction\n\nConvex optimization is the study of minimizing convex functions over convex sets. The theory is elegant and the algorithms are efficient, making convex optimization a cornerstone of modern applied mathematics.\n\n### Convex Sets and Functions\n\n::: {#def-convex-set}\n## Convex Set\nA set $C \\subseteq \\R^n$ is **convex** if for all $\\bx, \\by \\in C$ and $\\theta \\in [0, 1]$:\n$$\n\\theta \\bx + (1 - \\theta) \\by \\in C\n$$\n:::\n\n::: {#def-convex-function}\n## Convex Function\nA function $f: \\R^n \\to \\R$ is **convex** if for all $\\bx, \\by \\in \\R^n$ and $\\theta \\in [0, 1]$:\n$$\nf(\\theta \\bx + (1 - \\theta) \\by) \\leq \\theta f(\\bx) + (1 - \\theta) f(\\by)\n$$\n:::\n\n### Optimality Conditions\n\n::: {#thm-first-order}\n## First-Order Optimality\nLet $f: \\R^n \\to \\R$ be convex and differentiable. Then $\\bx^*$ is a global minimizer if and only if:\n$$\n\\nabla f(\\bx^*) = \\mathbf{0}\n$$\n:::\n\n::: {#thm-second-order}\n## Second-Order Condition\nA twice-differentiable function $f$ is convex if and only if its Hessian is positive semidefinite everywhere:\n$$\n\\nabla^2 f(\\bx) \\succeq 0 \\quad \\text{for all } \\bx\n$$\n:::\n\n### Quadratic Programming\n\n::: {#def-qp}\n## Quadratic Program\nA **quadratic program** (QP) is an optimization problem of the form:\n$$\n\\begin{aligned}\n\\min_{\\bx} \\quad & \\frac{1}{2} \\bx^\\top \\mathbf{P} \\bx + \\mathbf{q}^\\top \\bx \\\\\n\\text{s.t.} \\quad & \\bA \\bx = \\mathbf{b} \\\\\n& \\mathbf{G} \\bx \\leq \\mathbf{h}\n\\end{aligned}\n$$\nThe problem is convex if $\\mathbf{P} \\succeq 0$.\n:::\n\n### Exercises\n\n::: {#exr-least-squares}\n## Least Squares as QP\nShow that the least squares problem $\\min_\\bx \\norm{\\bA\\bx - \\mat